==English==
'''etymology''' 
Middle English ''pissen'' < Old French ''pissier'', probably of echoic origin.
===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''piss''' ([[uncountable]])

#(''vulgar'') [[Urine]]. 
#:''My third grade teacher told us to [[go]] now or forever hold our piss.''
#(''vulgar slang'') Alcoholic beverage, especially of inferior quality.
===Intransitive Verb===
[[Category:English intransitive verbs]]
{{en-infl-reg-sibilant|piss||}}
# to urinate

===Transitive Verb===
[[Category:English transitive verbs]]
{{en-infl-reg-sibilant|piss||}}
# to discharge as or with the urine

